        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 4:15PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 414 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers along a line
extending from near Little Falls to near Jordanville to Richfield
Springs. Movement was southeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Ingham Mills, Spinnerville, Beekman Corners, West Richmondville,
Countryman, Jordanville, Engleville, Gardnersville, Mindenville,
Kelhi Corners, Shedd Corners, Ripple Corners, McKinley, Herkimer,
Janesville, West Saint Johnsville, McCoon Crossing, Smith Corners,
Schuyler Corners, and Dolgeville.

This includes Interstate 90 between exits 29 and 30.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
eastern and east central New York.</instruction>
